description: Manual test case generation in structured JSON format
requirement: User should be able to log in using email and password.
prompt_used:
You are a senior QA engineer. Generate detailed manual test cases for the following requirement:

User should be able to log in using email and password.

Return the output **only in valid JSON** format (no explanations, no markdown). The JSON must be an array of objects, where each object has the following structure:

[
  {
    "test_case": "Unique ID or Title of the test case",
    "objective": "Purpose of this test case",
    "preconditions": ["Any preconditions required"],
    "test_data": ["List of test data items"],
    "test_steps": ["Step 1", "Step 2", "..."],
    "expected_results": ["Expected result 1", "Expected result 2"],
    "variations": ["Optional variations if any"],
    "edge_cases": ["Edge cases or negative tests"]
  }
]

⚠️ Important: Do not include any text outside of the JSON. Do not include markdown. Make sure it is valid JSON.

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify that user can log in using email and password.
preconditions: User has a registered account with valid email and password.
test_steps: Enter test user email in the 'Email' field.
Enter test user password in the 'Password' field.
expected_results: User is successfully logged in and redirected to the dashboard.
Application displays an error message if login credentials are incorrect.
edge_cases: Test with different browsers (e.g., Chrome, Firefox).
Test with different screen sizes and resolutions.

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify that application displays an error message when login credentials are incorrect.
preconditions: User has a registered account with valid email and password.
test_steps: Enter test user email in the 'Email' field.
Enter test user password (invalid) in the 'Password' field.
expected_results: Application displays an error message indicating incorrect credentials.
User is not logged in and remains on the login page.

structured_test_cases.objective: Verify that multiple users can log in simultaneously using email and password.
preconditions: Multiple users have registered accounts with valid emails and passwords.
test_steps: Enter test user email in the 'Email' field for each user.
Enter test user password in the 'Password' field for each user.
Click on the 'Login' button for each user.
expected_results: All users are successfully logged in and redirected to their respective dashboards.
Application does not display any error messages for multiple logins.
